[background arg="res://Bg/hallway.png" fade="1.0"]
audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/suspicious.mp3" [loop="true"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S1/The_hallway_buzzes_with_whispered.mp3" volume="0.0"]
The hallway buzzes with whispered conversations. Students cluster in groups, shooting glances toward the council room.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S1/The_protagonist_notices_the_unusual.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	The protagonist notices the unusual atmosphere while walking to class.
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S1/Mark_rushes_up.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Mark rushes up, slightly out of breath.
	Mark: Celestine! There you are. Did you hear?
	Celestine: Hear what? Everyone's acting strange today.
	Mark: The Student Council fund is missing. Twenty thousand pesos. Gone.
	Celestine: The outreach fund? For students who need supplies?
	Mark: That's the one. Ria discovered it this morning when she went to prepare the distribution list.
	Mark: The lockbox was empty. Not a single peso left.
	Celestine: That's a lot of money. When did this happen?
	Mark: Sometime yesterday evening, after classes. The principal already called an emergency meeting.
	Celestine: Who had access to the lockbox?
	Mark: That's the problem. The key is kept in Ms. Santos's desk drawer in the faculty room.
	Mark: Only she and the council officers know that.
	<Empty Text Event>
	Celestine: So it was either someone with inside knowledge, or...
	Mark: Or someone who figured it out. But here's the worst part.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S1/Mark_lowers_his_voice.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	audio music -
	Mark lowers his voice.
	audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/suspicious2.mp3" [loop="true"]
	Mark: Everyone's blaming Ria. Saying the treasurer must have taken it.
	Celestine: That's a serious accusation. Is there any evidence?
	Mark: Nothing solid. Just... she had access. She's the treasurer. People are connecting dots that might not exist.
	Celestine: Circumstantial at best. That's not proof of guilt.
	Mark: I know. But the rumors are spreading fast. I saw her crying in the bathroom earlier.
	Mark: Some kids were calling her a thief to her face.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S1/The_protagonist_expression_hardens.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	The Protagonist's expression hardens.
	Celestine: We can't let someone be condemned without proper evidence.
	Celestine: If Ria is innocent, she deserves someone to find the truth.
	Mark: I was hoping you'd say that. So we're taking the case?
	Celestine: We're taking the case. Who else was in the building yesterday evening?
	Mark: I asked around. Ryan was in the computer lab until late. Something about printing budget documents.
	Mark: And Ms. Santos was grading papers in the faculty room. She keeps the key to her drawer there.
	Celestine: Anyone else?
	Mark: Actually... I heard Alex was here too. Staying late for some club thing.
	Celestine: Alex? The former treasurer?
	Mark: Yeah. Ria replaced her last year. Some people say Alex took it personally.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S1/The_protagonist_considers_this_for_a_moment.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	The Protagonist considers this for a moment.
	Celestine: So we have three people with potential access... and two of them have reasons to resent the current council.
	Mark: Who do we talk to first?
	Celestine: Ryan. The computer lab is on the way. Then Alex. Let's see what they know.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	Conrad notices the unusual atmosphere as he walks to class.
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S1/Mark_rushes_up.mp3" volume="0.0"]
